sql:
SELECT COUNT(*) AS unresolved_feedback_count
FROM survey_feedback
WHERE is_resolved = 0;

SELECT age_group_id, SUM(total_count) AS total_respondents
FROM survey_results
GROUP BY age_group_id;

SELECT AVG(average_rating) AS avg_rating
FROM survey_results
WHERE age_group_id = 1;

external_knowledge:
- Average ratings are measured on a scale of 1-5; 
- A rating greater than 3.5 is generally considered positive; 
- Survey results can provide insights into the opinions and demographics of respondents.
